vulnerability.name: USN-5434-1
vulnerability.description: It was discovered that the methods of an Array object could be corrupted as a result of prototype pollution by sending a message to the parent process. If a user were tricked into opening a specially crafted website, an attacker could exploit this to execute JavaScript in a privileged context.

statements.status_notes: Firefox could be made to execute JavaScript in a privileged context if it opened a malicious website.
